<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>
<addons><addon id="plugin.program.orderfavourites" name="Order Favourites" version="1.5.2" provider-name="doko">
  <requires>
    <import addon="xbmc.python" version="3.0.0" />
  </requires>
  <extension point="xbmc.python.pluginsource" library="default.py">
    <provides>executable</provides>
  </extension>
  <extension point="xbmc.addon.metadata">
    <news>
[COLOR lavender][B]Order Favourites[/B][/COLOR]
[B]1.5.2:[/B]
- Added buttons to the dialog so you can change the rearranging mode: "Swap item A and B", or
"Re-insert A before B".
- Added a "How to use" button to the dialog with instructions.
- Long-pressing / right-clicking on an item in the grid will bring up a menu with more
options (most to first position, move to last position, type in specific position).

[B]1.4.0:[/B]
- Updated the dialog XML file to include explicit widths and Estuary default values. This makes
the dialog look the same on different skins.

[B]1.3.0:[/B]
- Changed the movement method to "Swap item A and B". The old method used to be
"Remove A and re-insert it around B", confusing and disruptive.

[B]1.2.3:[/B]
- Add-on metadata update with an icon fix.

[B]1.2.2:[/B]
- Ported the improvements from the Leia version to the Matrix version.

[B]1.2.1:[/B]
- Renamed "Save and exit" to "Save and reload", makes it clearer.
- Added "Save and exit". Use this when save + reload happens to crash your Kodi. After saving, restart Kodi manually to see the changes.
- Experimental Matrix version now available.

[B]1.2.0:[/B]
- Fixed a case when the add-on failed to read the favourites file because of Unicode strings.
(Thanks to [I]msauers[/I] for the report.)
- Changed the label and description of the 'Restart...' button to 'Restore...', which is
clearer.

[B]1.1.1:[/B]
- Added menu items for a more traditional add-on UX.
- Improved the profile reloading process.

[B]1.1.0:[/B]
- Improved the profile reloading process, it was crashing on Kodi 17.6.

[B]1.0.4:[/B]
- Safer handling of unicode text.
- Optimizations, simplified the code even more.

[B]1.0.3:[/B]
- Added a proper custom dialog interface.
- Greatly simplified the code, much faster to use.

[B]1.0.2:[/B]
- Fix for when the favorite item has unicode text.
    </news>
    <description lang="en">
Lets you reorder the entries in your Favourites.
Use this to organize your Favourites.
    </description>
    <platform>all</platform>
    <assets>
        <icon>icon.png</icon>
    </assets>
  </extension>
